    "comment": "Rationale: Voltage clamp experiments in the Calyx of Held using the specific blocker for Kv1.2 TsTX-Kalpha. Note that in this study the Kv1.2 channels are presynaptically very close to but not in the Calyx terminal.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has voltage-gated ion channel activity and is localized in teh presynaptic membrane (show with high-resolution technique). The inference to term 'voltage-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential (GO:0099508)' is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[P63142] SyNGO ID 183 (PMID:14614103, confocal). Experimental description: MM: p.28: Cochlear nucleus and brainstem slices (100-150 mm thick) were prepared as previously described (Rusznak et al. 1997; Dodson et al. 2002). 8-14 day old Wistar and Lister Hooded rats were killed by decapitation in accordance with the UK Animals -- Highlighted 15 Feb 2017",
